commitResults.messageBody:
Level 2. Add, List
Added the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Add the ability to change the status back to not done.

Incomplete Butler Level 4
Added 3 Task subtypes:
- Deadline class
- Event class
- ToDo class

Added toString method to Task class

Complete Butler Level 4
- Restructured Input Handling Blocks
- Completed toString() overridden methods for Deadline, Event and ToDo classes

Added Test Cases for Behavior for Deadlines , ToDos, and Events
- Creation (adding to list)
- Marking
- Unmarking
- Listing

Handled Errors
-Invalid Inputs for Deadline, ToDo, Events, such as empty description or empty date/time
-Invalid commands such as blah that have are not tied to Butler actions
-Invalid inputs for mark and unmark commands such as marking or unmarking an item in the list that does not exist, or following mark and unmark with multiple integers or non-integers

-Added try and catch block for NumberFormatExceptions in mark, delete and unmark sections of handleCommands

- Added testing and methods for deleting Tasks off the task ArrayList, catching the same exceptions as marking and unmarking Tasks in the list.
Added the use of enums and switch statements in the handleCommand method for better refactorability in later iterations.
